Add new Zod schemas and extend existing schemas in `packages/extension-api/src/manifest-schema.ts` to support non-secret settings declarations, placeholder hints on secrets, and group-based organization.

## Implementation Steps

### 1. Add SettingOptionSchema

Add this schema after the existing `SecretDeclarationSchema` definition:

```typescript
/** Option for select-type settings. */
export const SettingOptionSchema = z.object({
  label: z.string().min(1),
  value: z.union([z.string(), z.number()]),
});
```

### 2. Add SettingDeclarationSchema

```typescript
/** Non-secret configuration field declared in the manifest. */
export const SettingDeclarationSchema = z.object({
  /** Field type: text, number, boolean, or select. */
  type: z.enum(['text', 'number', 'boolean', 'select']),
  /** Setting key name (lowercase snake_case). */
  key: z.string().regex(/^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$/),
  /** Human-readable label for the settings UI. */
  label: z.string().min(1),
  /** Help text shown in the settings UI. */
  description: z.string().optional(),
  /** Placeholder text for text and number inputs. */
  placeholder: z.string().optional(),
  /** Default value used when no user override is stored. */
  default: z.union([z.string(), z.number(), z.boolean()]).optional(),
  /** Whether the extension cannot function without this setting. */
  required: z.boolean().default(false),
  /** Group name for collapsible section organization. */
  group: z.string().optional(),
  /** Options for select-type fields. */
  options: z.array(SettingOptionSchema).optional(),
  /** Minimum value for number-type fields. */
  min: z.number().optional(),
  /** Maximum value for number-type fields. */
  max: z.number().optional(),
});
```

### 3. Extend SecretDeclarationSchema with placeholder and group

Update the existing `SecretDeclarationSchema` (currently at lines 4-13) to add two new optional fields:

```typescript
const SecretDeclarationSchema = z.object({
  key: z.string().regex(/^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*$/),
  label: z.string().min(1),
  description: z.string().optional(),
  /** Custom placeholder hint for the password input (e.g., 'lin_api_xxxx'). */
  placeholder: z.string().optional(),
  required: z.boolean().default(false),
  /** Group name for collapsible section organization. */
  group: z.string().optional(),
});
```

These are additive optional fields, so existing manifests without them continue to parse correctly.

### 4. Add settings to ServerCapabilitiesSchema

Update `ServerCapabilitiesSchema` (currently at lines 30-37) to add the `settings` array:

```typescript
const ServerCapabilitiesSchema = z.object({
  serverEntry: z.string().default('./server.ts'),
  externalHosts: z.array(z.string().url()).optional(),
  secrets: z.array(SecretDeclarationSchema).optional(),
  /** Non-secret configuration fields (drives auto-generated settings UI). */
  settings: z.array(SettingDeclarationSchema).optional(),
});
```

### 5. Export new inferred types

Add these type exports alongside the existing `SecretDeclaration`, `DataProxyConfig`, `ServerCapabilities` exports at the bottom of the file (currently lines 66-69):

```typescript
export type SettingOption = z.infer<typeof SettingOptionSchema>;
export type SettingDeclaration = z.infer<typeof SettingDeclarationSchema>;
```

The `SecretDeclaration` and `ServerCapabilities` types update automatically via `z.infer` since they reference the modified schemas.

### 6. Make SettingOptionSchema and SettingDeclarationSchema exported

Both new schemas must use `export const` (not just `const`) since they are referenced externally for validation. The existing `SecretDeclarationSchema` is currently not exported (only the type is). Keep that pattern: export the schemas only if needed for runtime validation outside the module, otherwise export only the types.

However, `SettingDeclarationSchema` and `SettingOptionSchema` DO need to be exported for the server-side settings endpoint validation (Phase 2 will validate setting values against declared types). Export them:

```typescript
export const SettingOptionSchema = z.object({ ... });
export const SettingDeclarationSchema = z.object({ ... });
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- `SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse()` accepts all four field types (text, number, boolean, select) with their respective properties
- `SettingDeclarationSchema` rejects invalid key formats (uppercase, starting with number)
- `SettingDeclarationSchema` rejects invalid type values (e.g., 'password')
- `SecretDeclarationSchema` accepts `placeholder` and `group` as optional string fields
- `SecretDeclarationSchema` still works without `placeholder` and `group` (backward compatibility)
- `ServerCapabilitiesSchema` accepts `settings` alongside `secrets`
- `ServerCapabilitiesSchema` accepts `settings` without `secrets`
- All existing manifest tests continue to pass
- `SettingOption`, `SettingDeclaration` types are exported
- `SettingOptionSchema`, `SettingDeclarationSchema` are exported for runtime validation

Add comprehensive tests to `packages/extension-api/src/__tests__/manifest-schema.test.ts` covering all new schema additions: `SettingDeclarationSchema`, `SettingOptionSchema`, extended `SecretDeclarationSchema` with placeholder/group, and `ServerCapabilitiesSchema` with settings.

## Implementation Steps

Add three new `describe` blocks to the existing test file.

### 1. SettingDeclarationSchema tests

```typescript
import {
  ExtensionManifestSchema,
  SettingDeclarationSchema,
  SettingOptionSchema,
} from '../manifest-schema.js';

describe('SettingDeclarationSchema', () => {
  it('accepts a text setting with all fields', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: 'label_prefix',
      label: 'Label Prefix',
      description: 'Prefix for labels',
      placeholder: 'gh:',
      default: 'gh:',
      group: 'GitHub',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });

  it('accepts a number setting with min/max', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'number',
      key: 'refresh_interval',
      label: 'Refresh',
      default: 60,
      min: 10,
      max: 3600,
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });

  it('accepts a boolean setting with default', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'boolean',
      key: 'show_archived',
      label: 'Show Archived',
      default: false,
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });

  it('accepts a select setting with options', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'select',
      key: 'theme',
      label: 'Theme',
      options: [
        { label: 'Dark', value: 'dark' },
        { label: 'Light', value: 'light' },
      ],
      default: 'dark',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });

  it('accepts a minimal text setting (only required fields)', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: 'prefix',
      label: 'Prefix',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });

  it('defaults required to false', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: 'prefix',
      label: 'Prefix',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
    if (result.success) {
      expect(result.data.required).toBe(false);
    }
  });

  it('rejects invalid key format (uppercase)', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: 'InvalidKey',
      label: 'X',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(false);
  });

  it('rejects key starting with a number', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: '9key',
      label: 'X',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(false);
  });

  it('rejects invalid type', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'password',
      key: 'foo',
      label: 'X',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(false);
  });

  it('rejects empty label', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'text',
      key: 'foo',
      label: '',
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(false);
  });

  it('accepts select options with numeric values', () => {
    const result = SettingDeclarationSchema.safeParse({
      type: 'select',
      key: 'priority',
      label: 'Priority',
      options: [
        { label: 'Low', value: 1 },
        { label: 'High', value: 2 },
      ],
    });
    expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

